<text top="73" left="83" width="506" height="54" font="1">Learning goals revisited</text>
<text top="218" left="58" width="294" height="34" font="7">How does DNS work?</text>
<text top="254" left="166" width="796" height="34" font="12">DNS is a networked, hierarchical lookup that resolves an IP </text>
<text top="290" left="166" width="292" height="34" font="12">address which is vital </text>
<text top="326" left="58" width="855" height="34" font="7">Why are we moving away from DNS and what is the alternative?</text>
<text top="362" left="166" width="781" height="34" font="12">DNS is vulnerable to Man In The Middle attacks so we are </text>
<text top="398" left="166" width="432" height="34" font="12">moving towards using DNSSEC </text>
<text top="434" left="58" width="795" height="34" font="7">What is a certification authority and how does signing work?</text>
<text top="470" left="166" width="793" height="34" font="12">A group delegated trust ultimately by the US government to </text>
<text top="506" left="166" width="821" height="34" font="12">test the identity of people and confirm they are the owner of a </text>
<text top="542" left="166" width="625" height="34" font="12">public key by encrypting it with their private key</text>
</page>
